[{"id":32085,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4f4c998d-6e12-4300-9e2d-c04e6bb3349a-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 170px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/26ac6263-081b-4633-9861-efd5349de1b4-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 158px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a1c62f9e-94ba-43e3-a6b3-3239c4caa1d9-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 157px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ad2bd5cd-484a-4bb6-81c0-2c613ba1ea17-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 158px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PV</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>nRT</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">w</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mfrac><mi>RT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>dRT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></math> so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></math> Slope&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>RT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>Greater is slope greater is Temperature.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6ed24572-e6f8-4b99-8827-2433e0a84d64-image.png\" style=\"width: 160px; height: 152px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32130,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["Water $ < $ methyl alcohol $ < $ dimethyl ether $ < $ glycerol","methyl alcohol $ < $ glycerol $ < $ water $ < $ dimethyl ether","dimethyl ether $ < $ methyl alcohol $ < $ water $ < $ glycerol","glycerol $ < $ dimethyl ether $ < $ water $ < $ methyl alcohol"],"answer":2,"solution":"The correct order of viscosity of the given liquids is dimethyl ether $ < $ methyl alcohol $ < $ water $ < $ glycerol.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (23 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":32136,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["Straight line parallel to $x$-axis.","Straight line with a negative slope.","Curve starting at origin.","Straight line passing through origin."],"answer":1,"solution":"According to Boyle's law, $P V=$ constant\n$\\therefore \\log P+\\log V=$ constant\n$\\log P=-\\log V+$ constant\nHence, the plot of $\\log P$ vs $\\log V$ is straight line with negative slope.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (07 May Online)","image":null},{"id":32093,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>300</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>300</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup></mrow><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>927</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32097,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>Pb</mi><mi>RT</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8706;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi></mrow><mi>dP</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mi>RT</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32083,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Assuming ideal behaviour&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>dRT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mn>760</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>257</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>273</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>530</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>46</mn><mi>gm</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></math></p><p>So&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>46</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>082</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>530</mn></mrow><mn>100</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>760</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>151</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93</mn><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>152</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32149,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["$0.082$ litre atm","$0.987 \\mathrm{cal} \\mathrm{~mol}^{-1} \\mathrm{~K}^{-1}$","$8.3 \\mathrm{~J} \\mathrm{~mol}^{-1} \\mathrm{~K}^{-1}$","$83 \\mathrm{~erg} \\mathrm{~mol}^{-1} \\mathrm{~K}^{-1}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":32098,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>40</mn><mn>35</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mn>300</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>342</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>857</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>69</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>70</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8771;</mo><mn>70</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p><p>Hence answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>70</mn></mfenced></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32135,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["$u>v>\\alpha$","$v>u>\\alpha$","$\\alpha>u>v$","$u>\\alpha>v$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$$\n\\begin{aligned}\nu: v: \\alpha & =\\sqrt{\\frac{3 R T}{M}}: \\sqrt{\\frac{8 R T}{\\pi M}}: \\sqrt{\\frac{2 R T}{M}} \\\\\n& =\\sqrt{3}: \\sqrt{\\frac{8}{\\pi}}: \\sqrt{2}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n$$\n=1.224: 1.128: 1\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":32067,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["$4.26,19.3$","$2.59,11.85$","$5.46,17.8$","$2.96,11.2$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\frac{\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{N}_2}}{\\mathrm{Po}_2}=\\frac{\\mathrm{x}_{\\mathrm{N}_2} \\cdot \\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{T}}}{\\mathrm{x}_{\\mathrm{O}_2} \\cdot \\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{T}}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_{\\mathrm{N}_2}}{\\mathrm{n}_{\\mathrm{O}_2}}$ {using Dalton's law of partial pressure}<br />$\\begin{aligned} & =\\frac{70 / 28}{27 / 32}=2.96 \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{O}_2}}{\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{Ar}}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_{\\mathrm{O}_2}}{\\mathrm{n}_{\\mathrm{Ar}}}=\\frac{27 / 32}{3 / 40}=11.25\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (7 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32096,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Total moles of gases,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow><mn>44</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p><p>Now,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>nRT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>314</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>49652</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>149</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>652</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kPa</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>150</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kPa</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (17 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32133,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["$\\sqrt{2}: \\sqrt{3}: \\sqrt{8 / \\pi}$","$\\sqrt{2}: \\sqrt{8 / \\pi}: \\sqrt{3}$","$\\sqrt{8 / \\pi}: \\sqrt{3}: \\sqrt{2}$","$\\sqrt{3}: \\sqrt{8 / \\pi}: \\sqrt{2}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Most probable speed $\\left(C^*\\right)=\\sqrt{\\frac{2 R T}{M}}$ Average speed $(\\bar{C})=\\sqrt{\\frac{8 R T}{\\pi M}}$ Root mean square velocity $(C)=\\sqrt{\\frac{3 R T}{M}}$ $C^*: \\bar{C}: C=\\sqrt{2}: \\sqrt{\\frac{8}{\\pi}}: \\sqrt{3}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (26 May Online)","image":null},{"id":32090,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c74eb5f8-0774-401b-85e5-5a1eb06b678e-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 134px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e7b54a56-4891-4f6f-afc0-d9566cb93f5d-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 134px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4446806d-dd60-4094-aad0-1816ff745ae3-image.png\" style=\"width: 171px; height: 134px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5ca875d1-7414-4b9c-9945-882283c39f12-image.png\" style=\"width: 171px; height: 134px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"From ideal gas equation<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PV</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>nRT</mi></math>&nbsp;[At constant temperature for fixed amount of ideal gas]<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PV</mi><mo>=</mo></math>constant<br />So, As <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>&#8593;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>PV</mi></math> remain constant.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32099,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given mass<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math>Moles<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn></mrow><mn>26</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mol</mi></math></p><p>Temperature<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>273</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>323</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>740</mn><mn>760</mn></mfrac><mi>atm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0826</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#8467;</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>mol</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>nRT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn></mrow><mn>26</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0826</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>323</mn></mrow><mfenced><mfrac><mn>740</mn><mn>760</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>96314</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>078</mn></mrow><mn>19240</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0059</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#8467;</mi><mo>&#8771;</mo><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#8467;</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32100,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"&nbsp;if volume of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>cm</mi></math> balloon is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math><br />then volume of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mi>cm</mi></math> radius balloon <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>64</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math><br />So pressure will become <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>/</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>64</mn></math> times <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>48</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math> bar <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>750</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math> bar","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32071,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>From&nbsp;Boyle&#39;s Law,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>940</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;mm of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Hg</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo></math>&nbsp;Pressure at which volume is reduced by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo></math>&nbsp;Volume decreased by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Then,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>940</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1567</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>1567</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hg</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32111,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"Method <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>:<br />The extent of adsorption is directly proportional to the critical temperature. As <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;has&nbsp;the lowest critical temperature, it will have the lowest extent of adsorption.<br /><br />Method <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>:<br />The value of adsorption is dependent on the intermolecular forces of attraction. Among the given options, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> will have the weakest van der Waal&#39;s force (London Dispersion), in which only <math><mn>2</mn></math> electrons are involved.<br /><br />Hence, as a force of attraction is the weakest for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>,</mo></math> it will have the lowest adsorption value.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32109,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Critical temperature is :-</p><p><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>27</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br />for <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></math> the value of <math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math> is the highest so,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi></msub></math> for <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi></math> will be highest.<br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> for <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1.3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3.2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0.406</mn></math><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> for <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0.2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1.7</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0.118</mn></math><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> for <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>5.1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>5.1</mn></math><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> for <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4.1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0.82</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32082,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Applying ideal gas equation,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PV</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>nRT</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mi>where</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>pressure</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>volume</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Number</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>moles</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Universal</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>gas</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>constant</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Temperature</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>nRT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>760</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>18</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>32</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>29</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>21</mn></math>Litres</p><p>Hence, the volume of the box is 29 litres(In integer)</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32112,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PV</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ZnRT</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>ZnRT</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub></math><br /><br />At constant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math> and moles;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfrac></math><br />&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32103,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fb4ad1b4-fc89-4e61-83d4-9a34e1b6bbbb-image.png\" style=\"width: 247px; height: 189px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/956dbae0-55a0-4221-9985-5eca3cb1a5d3-image.png\" style=\"width: 252px; height: 188px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/09a6d910-16b5-4893-9644-05a04807d651-image.png\" style=\"width: 272px; height: 206px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2417bf82-5d90-4f31-b14e-1be8c6b952c1-image.png\" style=\"width: 252px; height: 191px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>A mixture of gases <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> and <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math> are taken in a closed vessel containing charcoal The graph that represents the correct behaviour of pressure with time is given below:</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/956dbae0-55a0-4221-9985-5eca3cb1a5d3-image.png\" style=\"width: 252px; height: 188px;\" /></p><p>Due to adsorption pressure of gas will decrease with time.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32144,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["50","25","37.5","53.5"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{B}}=\\mathrm{P}_{\\mathrm{B}}^{\\circ} \\times \\mathrm{B}=75 \\times \\frac{1}{1.5}=50$ torr","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":32129,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["Momentum and energy always remain conserved.","Pressure is the result of elastic collision of molecules with the container's wall.","Molecules are separated by great distances compared to their sizes.","All the molecules move in straight line between collision and with same velocity."],"answer":3,"solution":"Molecules move very fast in all directions in a straight line by colliding with each other but with different velocity.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (25 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":32094,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mfenced><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>PV</mi><mi>RT</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1000</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>083</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Weight of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>40</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>083</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>gm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>gm</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":32101,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>38</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>14</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>22</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi>gas</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>gas</mi></msub><mi>RT</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>&nbsp;constant so</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi>He</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>atm</mi></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi>Total</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi>He</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (03 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32078,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>PV</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>mix</mo></msub><mi>RT</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi>mix</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>083</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p>Out of total 3 moles Let mole of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>He</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></math></p><p>Mole of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></math></p><p>Then total mass of the mixture will be =&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p><p>Number of moles of He gas&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mol</mi></math></p><p>Mass of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>He</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>number</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>moles</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>molar</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mass</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":32146,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["intermolecular repulsions","intermolecular collisions per unit volume","Volume occupied by the molecules","intermolecular attraction"],"answer":2,"solution":"In Vander Waals equation ' $b$ ' is the excluded volume i.e. the volume occupied by the molecules","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":32120,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"States of Matter","question":"","options":["<math><mn>2</mn><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mn>2</mn><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math><mn>2</mn><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Given, two closed bulbs of equal volume<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;containing ideal gas initially of pressure <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi></math> temperature <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math>, which are connected by a narrow tube of negligible volume.<br /><br />To find the final pressure <math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi></mrow></msub></math>, when one raised to&nbsp;<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>:<br />Number&nbsp;of moles of gas does not change,<br />&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mtext>T</mtext></msub></mfenced><mtext>i</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mtext>T</mtext></msub></mfenced><mtext>f</mtext></msub></math><br /><math> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>P</mtext> <mtext>i</mtext> </msub> <mtext>V</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>RT</mtext> <mn>1</mn> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>P</mtext> <mtext>i</mtext> </msub> <mtext>V</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>RT</mtext> <mtext>1</mtext> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>P</mtext> <mtext>f</mtext> </msub> <mtext>V</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>RT</mtext> <mtext>1</mtext> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>P</mtext> <mtext>f</mtext> </msub> <mtext>V</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>RT</mtext> <mtext>2</mtext> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math><br /><math> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>P</mtext> <mtext>i</mtext> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>T</mtext> <mtext>1</mtext> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>P</mtext> <mtext>f</mtext> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mtext>T</mtext> <mtext>1</mtext> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> <mo>+</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mt